üí∞ Apple equipment will become more expensive from April 9 - what's going on.

The US is introducing new tariffs on technology from abroad, and this concerns not only Apple, but also Google and other American brands.

The first to be hit will be iPhone, MacBook, iPad and accessories - prices will increase as early as April 9 .

The reason is tariffs imposed as part of the trade policy initiated by the Trump administration. They apply to U.S. exports, which hits global supplies and logistics.

 What Apple can do:

‚Ä¢ Transfer of production to India . Currently, about 25% of iPhones are assembled there, but if India achieves a duty exemption and the share grows to 30%+, the price increase will be partially contained.
‚Ä¢ More pressure on suppliers to reduce the cost of components.
‚Ä¢ Trade-in programs may become more favorable to soften the impact on the consumer.

It is unlikely that the price increase will be avoided entirely - the industry is already reacting. This could slow down the introduction of new components and increase interest in more affordable devices such as the iPhone 16e.
